<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1884-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1884-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                        <head>No. 166.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">West</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1884-05-08"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 8,
                                1884</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Acknowledging the receipt of your note of
                            the 1st instant, in relation to a case of lynching in British Columbia
                            alleged to have been committed by American citizens from Washington
                            Territory, I have the honor to inform you that the matter is receiving
                            the attention of the Government.</p>
                        <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>